{"expireTime":9007200905935921000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-678e18417079031ca40ac5918188db9a-gatsby-remark-katexgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-images-medium-zoomgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypantsgatsby-remark-autolink-headersgatsby-remark-emoji-","val":"<p><br /><img src=\"/21b64a43b31dc28b05053c6d1c50f067/substrate.gif\" width=\"600\" height=\"300\">\n<br /><br /></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Introduction</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><br/> <strong>Substrate</strong> is blockchain framework that makes developer build their own blockchain easily. All of the <strong><em>Polkadot/Kusama parachains</em></strong> are built based on Substrate, which make networks multi-chain platform.</p>\n<p>One of the reason that Substrate makes build blockchain flexible is <strong>FRAME</strong>, an acronym for <strong><em>Framework for Runtime Aggregation of Modularized Entities</em></strong>. Here, we can see there is a word <em>Aggregation</em> meaning there are several modules for Runtime, which called <em>Pallets</em> that are hosting domain-specific logic.</p>\n<p><br />Here is overall architecture of Substrate Runtime<br />\n<br /><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 51.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"runtime architecture\" title=\"runtime architecture\" src=\"/static/87d7595109a5517df32d953769f5adbd/c1b63/runtime_architecture.png\" srcset=\"/static/87d7595109a5517df32d953769f5adbd/5a46d/runtime_architecture.png 300w,\n/static/87d7595109a5517df32d953769f5adbd/0a47e/runtime_architecture.png 600w,\n/static/87d7595109a5517df32d953769f5adbd/c1b63/runtime_architecture.png 1200w,\n/static/87d7595109a5517df32d953769f5adbd/10ab7/runtime_architecture.png 1552w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span></p>\n<h5 id=\"source-substrate\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#source-substrate\" aria-label=\"source substrate permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Source: Substrate</h5>\n<p><br /> As we can see, Substrate runtime is consist of several modules, which is called <strong>pallet</strong>. <strong>Pallet</strong> contains <em>types</em> for the config for the pallet that are used to logics in pallet, <em>storage items</em> to store the state of blockchain, <em>functions</em> for interacting with chain</p>\n<p><br />Here are Pallets <br />\n<br /><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 85.33333333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"pallet\" title=\"pallet\" src=\"/static/2013ed9c52b5b74cf0bfc0622342a363/c1b63/pallet.png\" srcset=\"/static/2013ed9c52b5b74cf0bfc0622342a363/5a46d/pallet.png 300w,\n/static/2013ed9c52b5b74cf0bfc0622342a363/0a47e/pallet.png 600w,\n/static/2013ed9c52b5b74cf0bfc0622342a363/c1b63/pallet.png 1200w,\n/static/2013ed9c52b5b74cf0bfc0622342a363/aa440/pallet.png 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span></p>\n<p><br /> If we want our chain to have certain feature, we can just choose the pallet that is related to the feature. For example, if we want Staking, then we choose Staking pallet. Of course, we can build our own Pallet. This is why Substrate is flexible.</p>\n<p>Now, I am going to do Substrate Tutorial called <strong><em>Kitties Workshop</em></strong>, which is to build full-stack NFT application with our own custom-pallet and some front-end pages</p>\n<br />\n<blockquote>\n<p>Kitties Workshop</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Custom Pallet</p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n<p>dfadf</p>"}